Mikhail Gorbachev was a visionary leader who brought about significant changes during his time as the leader of the USSR. He had the courage to acknowledge that the Cold War and communism needed to change, and he worked with President Reagan to reduce nuclear arsenals, bringing relief to people around the world. Gorbachev also embraced democratic reforms and believed in openness and restructuring as the way forward for the Soviet Union. These actions showed his rare leadership qualities and resulted in a safer world and greater freedom for millions of people. Even after leaving office, Gorbachev remained engaged in important work, such as reducing nuclear stockpiles. His contributions earned him high esteem worldwide, and his belief in a better world benefited people everywhere.